values:
It's not that often that a large pot of food I make gets polished off by the end of the day.&nbsp; The curry was just that omfg good!&nbsp; I might throw the salmon in later or defrost it first next time though.&nbsp; More tomato and onion would be good too.&nbsp; I don't think I'll be ordering curry at Thai places anymore.&nbsp; Maybe noodles, since I haven't successfully recreated a good healthy, low sodium version of it yet, but then again, I am better off without it.&nbsp; 

That Ethiopian place is really good though.&nbsp; And my face is on their wall from the review I did too!&nbsp; OMG!&nbsp; Totally weird...

A study in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seattle,_Washington" title="Seattle, Washington" class="mw-redirect">Seattle, Washington</a> showed that 100% of wild salmon had <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roundworm" title="Roundworm" class="mw-redirect">roundworm</a> larvae capable of infecting people, whereas the same study showed that farm-raised salmon did not have any roundworm larvae.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sashimi#cite_note-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup>&nbsp; bummer.&nbsp; I guess we'll stick to farmed then!

It's so depressing-
Snow sits on the ground outside.&nbsp; 
Damn this cold weather

The universe has reminded me yet again that getting started early on a project is a bad idea because people change their damn minds.

8 more llamas are in the works, assembly line style.&nbsp; Well, the sewing machine's needle snapped in 3 pieces and one piece went flying, luckily NOT into my eye.&nbsp; That's some dangerous shit!&nbsp; Turns out some thread had caught in that stupid little notch in the edge of the plastic spool it comes in.&nbsp; Good thing I bought a whole pack of the damn needles!&nbsp;&nbsp; With any luck, nothing else will be fucked up and I'll be able to finish a bunch tomorrow. 

I think I'm having an allergic reaction to my bed.&nbsp; Or rather, it's the deodorant Chad uses and rubs off on his side of the bed.&nbsp; This does not make me happy.&nbsp;
